<dl id="n05038i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05038i">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05038i"> 38(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Clothing of novices</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Apropos to this other stories followed. A novice once asked the meaning of the Scriptural passage &ldquo;He was <mark>clothed with curses as with a garment</mark>.&rdquo; &ldquo;It implies that he had got a habit of swearing,&rdquo; was the ready rejoinder. <small> William J. Fitz-Patrick, <a name="BURKE" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BURKE"><cite title="source">The Life of the Very Rev. Thomas N. Burke</cite></a>, (1885) II, 250</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
